HEADWORD: Orohippus
<hw>Or`o*hip"pus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>'o`ros</grk>, mountain (referring to the Rocky Mountain region) +
<grk>"i`ppos</grk> horse.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of
American Eocene mammals allied to the horse, but having four toes in
front and three behind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oroide</ent>⟦br⟧
